        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 10:16PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 1016 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Champion to 6 miles east of Wray. Movement
was southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

These storms will remain over mainly rural areas of east central Yuma
and Dundy Counties, including the following locations... Max.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
